Find the volume of a cylinder with radius 2x millimeters and height x - 2 millimeters.
a. [
V = pi * (2x)^2 * (x - 2)
]
[
V = 4pi * x^2 * (x - 2)
]
[
V = 4pi(x^3 - 2x^2)
]
b. If x = 10:
[
V = 4pi(1000 - 200) = 3200pi = 10,053.5 mm^3
]

Find the volume of a cylinder with diameter 6 cm shorter than the height x.
a. [
r = (x - 6)/2
]
[
V = pi * ((x - 6)/2)^2 * x
]
[
V = pi * (x - 6)^2 * x / 4
]
b. If height is 14 cm (so x = 14):
[
r = (14 - 6)/2 = 4 cm
]
[
V = pi * 16 * 14 = 224pi = 703.7 cm^3
]

Find the volume of a cylinder with radius x feet and height 3x + 4 feet.
a. [
V = pi * x^2 * (3x + 4)
]
[
V = pi(3x^3 + 4x^2)
]
b. If x = 3:
[
V = pi(3(27) + 4(9)) = pi(81 + 36) = 117pi = 367.6 ft^3
]

